x4freetext: COMPLETE DETAILS OF APPARATUS.
-ANGULAR DISTRIBUTIONS OF 230,232-TH(N,F) AND THE THIRD
MINIMUM HYPOTHESIS.
4 MV DYNAMITRON TANDEM ACCELERATOR,
DELIVERING AN MAXIMUM PROTON CURRENT OF 75 MICRO-AMPS.
TIME-OF-FLIGHT MEASUREMENT OF FISSION FRAGMENTS.
THE TOF SPECTRA FROM THE DIFFERENT DETECTORS ALL
SHOWED EXCELLENT DISCRIMINATION BETWEEN LIGHT AND
HEAVY FRAGMENTS, THOUGH ONLY LIGHT FRAGMENT DISTRI-
BUTIONS WERE OF INTEREST. HOWEVER THE HEAVY FRAGMENT
YIELD MEASURED AT THE DETECTOR ANGLE THETA CAN BE
TAKEN AS THE LIGHT FRAGMENT YIELD AT 180-THETA. THUS
THERE ARE A TOTAL OF 20 DATA POINTS FROM THE 10
DETECTORS.
FIVE 10.2 X 10.2 CM PARALLEL PLATE AVALANCHE
COUNTERS, HAVING A POSITION RESOLUTION OF +/-0.8 MM.
THEY WERE PLACED AT A DISTANCE OF 40 CM FROM THE
TARGET AND AT ANGLES OF 0, 45, +/-90, -107 AND -135
DEGREES WITH RESPECT TO THE PROTON BEAM DIRECTION.
TWO 900 MM2 AND THREE 300 MM2 F-SERIES ORTEC
SURFACE BARRIER DETECTORS. THEY WERE PLACED AT ANGLES
.THE RELATIVE EFFICIENCIES AND SOLID ANGLES OF ALL
DETECTORS WAS DETERMINED USING A 252-CF SOURCE ON
NICKEL BACKING IN PLACE OF THE FISSION TARGET. CAL-
IBRATIONS WERE PERFORMED BEFORE AND AFTER EACH (N,F)
RUN WITH BOTH THE SOURCE AND THEN THE BACKING FACING
THE ACCELERATION GRID. THE DETECTION EFFICIENCY OF
ALL DETECTORS WAS FOUND EQUAL FOR BOTH LIGHT AND
HEAVY FISSION FRAGMENTS.
.THE TIME REFERENCE SIGNAL FOR ALL THE DETECTORS WAS
PROVIDED BY A ONE CHANNEL PLATE ARRANGEMENT, PLACED
PERPENDICULAR TO THE TARGET OUT OF THE REACTION PLANE.
ELECTRONS KNOCKED OUT FROM THE TARGET WERE DEFLECTED
TO THE DETECTOR WITH AN ELECTROSTATIC MIRROR. BY THE
POSITION READ-OUT THE REACTION POINT IN THE TARGET
COULD BE DETERMINED WITH A RESOLUTION OF +/-1.5 MM.
.THE DATA WERE CORRECTED FOR ENERGY LOSSES IN THE
TARGET.
MAINLY DUE TO THE OPENING ANGLE OF THE CONE
OF EMITTED NEUTRONS RESULTING FROM THE CLOSE GEOMETRY
OF THE SET-UP, ASSESSED BY MONTE CARLO SIMULATION.

x4freetext: ANGULAR DISTRIBUTION OF
LIGHT FISSION FRAGMENT YIELD. DATA ARE THE RATIOS
YIELD(THETA)/YIELD(90DEG).
A 100 MICRO-G/CM2 METALLIC LITHIUM TARGET WITH
NATURAL ABUNDANCE, EVAPORATED ONTO AN ALUMINIUM HUT OF
16 MM DIAMETER. THE HUT WAS WATER-COOLED AND SERVED AS
A BEAM DUMP. NEARLY MONOENERGETIC NEUTRONS IN THE
RANGE 0.7 TO 3.3 MEV WERE PRODUCED WITH A RESOLUTION
OF 30 KEV AND A FLUX 1.7E+07 N/CM2 SEC THROUGH THE
FISSILE DEPOSIT.
.IN THIS EXPERIMENT THE PROTON BEAM WAS DEFOCUSSED TO A
DIAMETER OF 12 MM, GIVING AN UNCERTAINTY IN EN OF
ABOUT +/-20 KEV AND AN ANGLE SPREAD OF ABOUT +/-5 DEG.
.THE FISSION TARGET WAS STACKED FROM FOUR
140 MICRO-G/CM2 THF4 LAYERS, EACH EVAPORATED ONTO
25 MICRO-G/CM2 CARBON FOIL. THE TARGET WAS LOCATED
42 MM FROM THE NEUTRON PRODUCING TARGET.
.DATA OBTAINED FROM F.M.BAUMANN.
S.W.

x4freetext: ANGULAR DISTRIBUTION OF
LIGHT FISSION FRAGMENT YIELD. DATA ARE THE RATIOS
YIELD(THETA)/YIELD(90DEG).
A 100 MICRO-G/CM2 METALLIC LITHIUM TARGET WITH
NATURAL ABUNDANCE, EVAPORATED ONTO AN ALUMINIUM HUT OF
16 MM DIAMETER. THE HUT WAS WATER-COOLED AND SERVED AS
A BEAM DUMP. NEARLY MONOENERGETIC NEUTRONS IN THE
RANGE 0.7 TO 3.3 MEV WERE PRODUCED WITH A RESOLUTION
OF 30 KEV AND A FLUX 1.7E+07 N/CM2 SEC THROUGH THE
FISSILE DEPOSIT.
.IN THIS EXPERIMENT A WELL-FOCUSSED PROTON BEAM WAS
SCANNED OVER AN AREA OF 8 X 8 MM BY DEFLECTION
MAGNETS, THUS REDUCING THE UNCERTAINTIES. SAMPLING OF
THE INDUCTION CURRENTS GAVE THE POSITION OF THE PROTON
BEAM, THUS ENABLING THE NEUTRON DIRECTION ALSO TO BE
DETERMINED SINCE THE POSITION OF THE FISSION IN THE
FISSION TARGET IS ALSO MEASURED.
.THE FISSION TARGET WAS A FACE-TO-FACE SANDWICH OF TWO
510 MICRO-G/CM2 THF4 LAYERS ON 50 MICRO-G/CM2 CARBON.
THE TARGET WAS LOCATED 42 MM FROM THE NEUTRON
PRODUCING TARGET.
.DATA OBTAINED FROM F.M.BAUMANN.
S.W.
